CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 9, 1960, pg. 9, reads: "Luncheon Principals - Among the principal figures who sparked Pittsburgh's 16th annual Carver Week Luncheon, held in Webster Hall's Georgian Room Tuesday of this week were, left to right: Mrs. Alma Illery, president, National Achievement Clubs Inc., sponsors: the Rt. Rev. John J. Wright, Bishop of the Pittsburgh Catholic diocese, who gave the invocation; and Dr. Ethel J. Alpenfels, New York University staff, who delivered the main address. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Alma Illery, Bishop John J. Wright, and Dr. Ethel J. Alpenfels posed in Webster Hall for Carver Week luncheon
